# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ALLOWLIST .gitignore — deny everything, re-allow ONLY the public files,
# then hard-deny the private set LAST (in gitignore, the last matching rule
# wins, so these final denies beat any accidental overlapping allow).
#
# This working tree contains a private subsystem (the negotiator), logged-in
# session state, personal data, and the dev wiki. Publishing works by explicit
# allowlist so nothing new can ever reach the public repo by accident:
# a file that is not re-allowed below with a `!` rule CANNOT be committed.
# To publish a new file: add a `!` rule for it in section 2, deliberately.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# 1) Deny every file, everywhere…
*
# …but let git descend into directories (files inside stay denied until allowed).
!*/

# 2) Re-allow the public project, file by file.
!.gitignore
!README.md
!LICENSE
!requirements.txt
!config.example.json
!monitor.py
!prices.py
!config.py
!fb_marketplace.py
!vinted.py
!vendora_crawler.py
!applog.py
!ai_verify.py
!gpu_perf.py
!laptop_perf.py
!ram_specs.py
!ram_kits.json
!serve.py
!reports.py
!archive_store.py
!listing_common.py
!dashboard.html
!verify_dashboard.py
!Dockerfile
!docker-compose.yml
!.dockerignore
!tests/**
!.github/**
!docs/**

# 3) Hard-deny the private set — LAST, so these always win.
LIST LURKER/
repos/
Standalone/
recon_output/
negotiator_out/
logs/
job_data/
scratch/
backup_csv_*/
.claude/
.agents/
__pycache__/
.venv/
venv/
env/
negotiator*.py
ledger.py
pricing.py
gate_ai.py
targeting.py
poll_response.py
skoop_email.py
corrections.py
recon_*.py
Negotiation_strategy.md
negotiator_config.json
config.json
fb_state.json
skroutz_state.json
email_config.json
negotiations.json
pending_offers.json
message_corrections.json
data_reports.json
*.zip
*.docx
*.bak
*.bak_*
*.log
*.csv
msg_*.txt
job_scout_*.html
retail_debug.html

# 4) Deliberate exceptions to the `*.csv` deny above (last match wins):
#    sanitized sample data so a fresh clone has something to show, and the same
#    snapshot again under docs/ for the static GitHub Pages demo.
!sample_data/
!sample_data/*.csv
!docs/*.csv
